text: Nneka Ukuh (born November 20, 1987) is a female track and field athlete from Nigeria. She specialised in the high jump event, and is best known for winning the gold medal for her native West African country at the 2003 All-Africa Games. ==Competition record== {| |- !colspan="6"|Representing |- |rowspan=2|2003 |All-Africa Games |Abuja, Nigeria |bgcolor=gold|1st |1.84 m |- |Afro-Asian Games |Hyderabad, India |7th |1.70 m |- |2006 |African Championships |Bambous, Mauritius |bgcolor=silver|2nd |1.80 m |- |2007 |All- Africa Games |Algiers, Algeria |5th |1.79 m |- |2008 |African Championships |Addis Ababa, Ethiopia |4th |1.75 m |} ==References== * IAAF Profile Category:1987 births Category:Living people Category:Nigerian female high jumpers Category:African Games gold medalists for Nigeria Category:African Games medalists in athletics (track and field) Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2003 All-Africa Games Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2007 All-Africa Games
